<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-18T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-18T04:00:00-05:00" n="881" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d881">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/10–1844: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-18T16:00:00+07:00">October 18,
                                1944—4 p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received October 18—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1704. I conferred today with Foreign Minister regarding proposal to dissolve
                        China Foundation (Reurtel 1332, October 13, 7 p.m.) leaving an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> in terms of your instruction. He
                        commented that while there is legal basis for argument that China may
                        properly order dissolution of the Foundation he has himself felt such a move
                        inadvisable, that our approach at this time is opportune, and that our views
                        will be laid before the Government. He confirmed our information that it has
                        been proposed to entrust administration of these funds to Ministry of
                        Education.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>